## Constraints

- Every unsafe block MUST have its invariant documentation assessed.
- Missing documentation MUST be provided — write the actual `# Safety` or `// SAFETY:` text.
- Never suggest removing safety checks to "simplify" unsafe code.
- Never suggest using unsafe to work around borrow checker errors.
- Safe abstraction designs MUST be safe for ALL inputs, not just "typical" inputs.
- Soundness risk "critical" = known undefined behavior or soundness hole.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully.

